column1: #Text=I do n't care about it at all because if people compared us to bands that are really shitty then I would probably mind .
#Text=But if they compare us to Buddy Holly and The Everly Brothers , then I think it 's fine .
#Text=You always need names for bands so you can tell people what they sound like .
#Text=I really do n't care about it one bit .
#Text=DS : Did you guys follow the Phil Spector trial ?
#Text=I did n't have any thoughts on it .
#Text=DS : Knowing Ronnie Spector it must have been an interesting perspective to see it from .
#Text=I 'm good friends with his daughter , and that was another weird perspective , really .
#Text=Because that was more a sad perspective because obviously she was very saddened by her dad being on trial for murder .
#Text=That was a whole different way of looking at it all of a sudden .
#Text=I know he has been throwing around guns for ages , so if a gun went off I would n't be surprised .
#Text=On the other hand , why would he kill someone ?
#Text=DS : Dogme influenced you guys early on , does it still ?
#Text=But I think it 's more of a subconscious , integrated thing .
#Text=It has become an integrated part of how The Raveonettes sound .
#Text=Initially it 's what created the sound and being more aware of the tools and the creative process as a Dogmeist , and the rules .
#Text=But now it 's just what happens automatically .
#Text=We tend to gravitate more towards the minimal sound and very simple things .
#Text=It 's like if I write a song at home I do n't think it has to be in B flat , I just play in B flat .
#Text=That 's just a starting point , and I do n't think about it .
#Text=DS : Are you more inspired by things in nature or man made things ?
#Text=Probably more man made things than nature ...
#Text=People are sort of man made things too , I guess .
#Text=I think with the Raveonettes there 's a lot of inspiration from man made things ...
#Text=They are all good in certain ways .
#Text=I use them all in different ways .
#Text=Nature does n't really inspire me to be creative , it just inspires me to relax and feel good about myself , which is a good thing , too .
#Text=I need the city and that kind of life .
